                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/comments/3411271265"
                }
            },
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "My issue is the relation between `trigger_resize` and `windows_list`. Your patch  explicitly requires both while Nvim assumes `windows_list` is always set regardless of the codepath.\r\n\r\nIf the Vim patch moved the check inside like \r\n\r\n```\r\n// If both are to be triggered do WinResized first.\r\nif (trigger_resize) {\r\n        // ...\r\n\tif (windows_list != NULL && dict_add_list(v_event, \"windows\", windows_list) == OK) {\r\n        }\r\n        // ...\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nthen the patch would be less controversial to me when comparing Vim vs Nvim.",
            "commit_id": "e8ab90dcc3d0d51bc51f96b1d1a5e250c62bf235",
            "created_at": "2026-06-15T05:48:35Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -6112,7 +6112,7 @@ void may_trigger_win_scrolled_resized(void)\n   }\n \n   // If both are to be triggered do WinResized first.\n-  if (trigger_resize) {\n+  if (trigger_resize && windows_list != NULL) {",
